<SiteLayout
  title="Sweep Pro Trackpad: Keep Pointer Actions on the Keyboard | NXTKB"
  description="A read-aloud script for the Sweep Pro trackpad: what it solves, how to use it, and where it fits in daily pointer work."
>
  <section class="hero article-hero" style="--hero-image: url('/products/ferris-sweep-pro/trackpad.png')">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="eyebrow">Sweep Pro Trackpad</p>
      <h1>Keep pointer actions on the keyboard</h1>
      <p>The goal is not to replace every mouse. It is to reduce small, frequent reaches for cursor movement, clicks, scrolling, horizontal scrolling, and basic drag work.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <article class="article">
    <div class="article-body">
      <p class="article-lede">
        Hi, in this post I want to talk about the trackpad on Sweep Pro. At first glance, it is just a round touch area on the right half of the keyboard. But the real point is not the extra hardware. The real point is how it changes the way you use a mouse while typing.
      </p>

      <div class="video-embed" aria-label="Video embed placeholder">
        <div class="video-placeholder">
          <strong>The video will be embedded here after publishing.</strong>
          <span>Replace this block with a YouTube, Bilibili, or other platform iframe when the video is ready.</span>
        </div>
